We’re back from a long hiatus and excited to share the many projects we’ve been working on this past year.

Introducing the Brick House, a new multi-family building that is nested within the red masonry perimeter walls of an old industrial building.

Large expanses of sliding glass doors connect the various spaces to the outdoors, while the use of a light-toned brick throughout the project creates a sense of continuity and permanence.

Many thanks to @ad_italia for the feature on one of our recently completed projects, the Hosono House.

Voluminous, geometric, and light-filled, the house has a playful treehouse-like quality, while being furnished with an eclectic mix of vintage designer pieces thoughtfully collected by the owners, @wjf3 and @kaishh 

And special thanks to the amazing team who worked on this project and who helped make the vision come to life ✨
